        type: 'mendelian_genetics',
        context: { difficulty: 'beginner', topic: 'Mendelian Genetics', focus: 'segregation' },
        subparts: [
            'Law of Segregation:',
            '  - Allele pairs separate during gamete formation (meiosis)',
            '  - Each gamete receives only ONE allele from each pair',
            '  - Random which allele goes to which gamete',
            '',
            'Example with Aa parent:',
            '  Parent genotype: Aa',
            '  During meiosis: Alleles separate',
            '  Gametes produced:',
            '    - 50% carry A',
            '    - 50% carry a',
            '',
            'Why Important:',
            '  - Explains 3:1 ratio in F2 generation',
